Selenium Locators

1) There are total 8 locators in selenium 

2) In selenium 4.0, RelativeLocators introduce.

-----------Selenium Locators ------------------
   a) id
   b) name
   c) xPath
   d) cssSelector
   e) tagName
   f) linkText
   g) partialLinkText
   h) className
   i) Relative Locator: above, below, near, toRightOf, toLeftof

3) id : Id is the always first preference. It is the fastest locator in selenium and mostly unique locator

4) xPath & cssSelector: Very frequently used locators because user can defined unique and handle dynamic locator. 
                        It is not mandatory all elements will have id, name, className etc.
                        We need to follow the syntax to use xPath & cssSelector
                        
5) Straight forward locator: id, name, tagName, linkText, partialLinkText, className

